482
00:48:36,847 --> 00:48:43,582
Listen, buddy, could you
do me a favor and just get
a little rest?

483
00:48:43,654 --> 00:48:47,590
I know that you are working
very, very hard on this
repatch...

484
00:48:47,658 --> 00:48:52,254
but there's no reason to push
yourself to do another
engine-burn test tomorrow.

485
00:48:54,031 --> 00:48:57,330
Between you and me,
you have got plenty of time...

486
00:48:57,434 --> 00:49:02,633
so let's just put it off
for a day or two.

487
00:49:05,642 --> 00:49:09,009
Go to the beach,
drink a Mai Tai.

488
00:49:09,112 --> 00:49:12,013
Just take a day off, okay?

489
00:49:12,115 --> 00:49:14,743
Bob out.

490
00:49:14,818 --> 00:49:19,312
I got about six more hours
on this repatch...

491
00:49:19,389 --> 00:49:24,292
but we are doing this
engine-burn test tomorrow
come hell or high water.

492
00:49:27,364 --> 00:49:28,956
That's all I got.

493
00:49:29,032 --> 00:49:30,522
Life One out.

494
00:49:32,469 --> 00:49:35,927
This is engine-burn
connection test number two.

495
00:49:36,006 --> 00:49:41,638
Arming... in three, two, one.

496
00:50:06,870 --> 00:50:08,497
Fuck!

497
00:50:12,743 --> 00:50:14,802
This fucking--

498
00:50:39,202 --> 00:50:44,162
Bob, I'm becoming concerned
about the failure of these
engine-burn tests.

499
00:50:45,742 --> 00:50:49,178
I'm worried about the
ramifications.

500
00:52:34,684 --> 00:52:41,180
We've got, uh...
about 2,500 calories...

501
00:52:41,258 --> 00:52:45,718
taken in today and about
1 1 minutes calisthenics.

502
00:52:54,171 --> 00:53:00,167
There's a sound coming from the
hibernation and reentry capsule.

503
00:53:02,445 --> 00:53:04,845
I don't know what it is.

504
00:53:08,418 --> 00:53:13,879
Could you... take a look
at that for me?

505
00:53:13,957 --> 00:53:18,485
Or give me some ideas
about what that could be?

506
00:53:22,199 --> 00:53:24,099
Thanks.

507
00:53:24,201 --> 00:53:25,896
Life One out.

508
00:53:39,049 --> 00:53:41,244
Michael, this is Bob.

509
00:53:41,318 --> 00:53:46,278
There is no reason that there
should be any sound coming
from the capsule.

510
00:53:46,389 --> 00:53:47,754
The capsule is dead.

511
00:53:47,824 --> 00:53:49,052
Now, listen to me.

512
00:53:49,125 --> 00:53:52,219
You are not sleeping.

513
00:53:52,295 --> 00:53:56,425
One friend to another,
you look like hell, bro.

514
00:53:56,499 --> 00:54:01,402
So, get some rest, continue
eating, continue exercising.

515
00:54:01,471 --> 00:54:07,376
You have to exercise not just
your body, Michael, but your
mind and get some rest.

516
00:54:07,444 --> 00:54:10,470
That's my advice to you today.
Bob out.

517
00:54:22,325 --> 00:54:24,486
Shut up, Nathan!
Shut up!

518
00:54:24,594 --> 00:54:26,653
Goddamn it!

519
00:54:30,700 --> 00:54:31,724
God--!

520
00:55:07,637 --> 00:55:12,336
This is engine-burn test
number seven, three, two, one.

521
00:55:24,821 --> 00:55:27,483
This is engine-burn test
number eight...

522
00:55:27,557 --> 00:55:31,288
in three, two, one.

523
00:55:38,535 --> 00:55:43,131
Test number 1 1
in three, two, one.

524
00:55:46,242 --> 00:55:51,680
Number 1 4... in three, two, one.

525
00:55:58,788 --> 00:56:01,518
Three, two, one.

526
00:56:12,435 --> 00:56:15,268
In three, two, one.

527
00:56:31,788 --> 00:56:34,586
This is engine-burn test
number 25...

528
00:56:34,657 --> 00:56:38,184
in three, two, one.

529
00:56:45,301 --> 00:56:46,859
Oh, baby.

530
00:57:02,819 --> 00:57:05,720
Come on, come on, come on.

531
00:57:10,760 --> 00:57:12,057
God--

532
00:57:14,964 --> 00:57:17,330
No, no, no, no, no!

533
00:57:40,156 --> 00:57:41,623
No, no.

534
00:57:42,859 --> 00:57:47,319
1 632, 1 634...

535
00:57:47,397 --> 00:57:49,160
no, that's all right.

536
00:57:49,232 --> 00:57:50,995
Goddamn it, come on!

537
00:58:03,012 --> 00:58:05,810
Wasn't a-- wasn't
a frayed wire, was it?

538
00:58:05,882 --> 00:58:09,283
S-20, S-26, 27.

539
00:58:14,491 --> 00:58:15,958
Ugh, it's not here.

540
00:58:18,928 --> 00:58:20,987
Fuck, it's cold.

541
00:58:33,109 --> 00:58:36,408
No, no, no, that's fine.
It's fine.

542
00:58:36,513 --> 00:58:39,573
This isn't it.
This isn't it.

543
00:58:42,719 --> 00:58:43,708
Come on.

544
00:59:39,442 --> 00:59:42,377
Guidance systems, check.

545
00:59:42,445 --> 00:59:45,573
Guidance system, check.

546
00:59:47,650 --> 00:59:49,914
Hey, look, pal...

547
00:59:49,986 --> 00:59:53,752
there's nobody else I'd rather
do this mission with.

548
00:59:53,823 --> 00:59:55,290
I mean that.

549
01:00:05,034 --> 01:00:06,831
Let's do this.

550
01:00:46,876 --> 01:00:48,867
What are you doing?

551
01:00:52,649 --> 01:00:54,810
This ain't the man I know.

552
01:00:57,887 --> 01:01:01,983
Get the fuck up... Michael!

553
01:01:02,058 --> 01:01:02,956
Michael, get up!

554
01:02:29,278 --> 01:02:33,977
Michael, you--
you son of a bitch.

555
01:02:34,083 --> 01:02:39,646
I-- I cannot believe
that you made it.

556
01:02:39,756 --> 01:02:42,418
Uh, I lost a lot of money.

557
01:02:42,492 --> 01:02:45,655
Um, be well, we'll do
the work we need to here...

558
01:02:45,762 --> 01:02:48,322
and, uh, send us a message
when you can.

559
01:02:48,431 --> 01:02:50,126
Bob out.

560
01:02:54,303 --> 01:02:59,297

Yeah, I made it.

561
01:03:00,643 --> 01:03:02,804
I'm alive anyway.

562
01:03:05,615 --> 01:03:06,980
So what's next?

563
01:03:09,118 --> 01:03:14,522
I still have a post-Venus
engine burn ahead...

564
01:03:14,624 --> 01:03:18,321
and have yet to perform
a successful test.

565
01:03:22,198 --> 01:03:26,328
And if I do get all the way
back to Earth...

566
01:03:26,402 --> 01:03:28,700
I have to crawl back
into that capsule...

567
01:03:28,805 --> 01:03:35,472
and hope that whatever
rudimentary interior repair
I do...

568
01:03:35,545 --> 01:03:37,536
won't rupture on reentry.

569
01:03:42,852 --> 01:03:44,513
And before that can happen...

570
01:03:47,223 --> 01:03:49,691
I have years of this.

571
01:03:52,695 --> 01:03:54,686
For what?

572
01:03:54,764 --> 01:03:58,291
To say... I survived?

573
01:04:03,039 --> 01:04:06,497
Sometimes I think...

574
01:04:06,576 --> 01:04:12,037
if I could get these
engines fired up at all.

575
01:04:15,117 --> 01:04:17,745
Maybe I shouldn't stop at Earth.

576
01:04:22,358 --> 01:04:24,758
Maybe I should...

577
01:04:24,861 --> 01:04:28,991
ride this thing...
all the way to Europa.

578
01:04:33,369 --> 01:04:37,100
In a lot of ways...
I'm dead already.

579
01:04:41,477 --> 01:04:45,277
Otherwise... yeah...

580
01:04:47,817 --> 01:04:48,749
I made it...

581
01:04:52,054 --> 01:04:53,919
but what's the point?

582
01:04:59,829 --> 01:05:02,764
Astronaut Forrest, I just
want to thank you so much...

583
01:05:02,832 --> 01:05:07,201
for being a tremendous
influence to me and my family.

584
01:05:07,270 --> 01:05:08,737
We're so proud of you.

585
01:05:08,804 --> 01:05:10,465
We wish you the very best...

586
01:05:10,573 --> 01:05:12,905
and please,
have a safe journey home.

587
01:05:12,975 --> 01:05:16,741
You're my hero.

588
01:07:05,121 --> 01:07:07,749
Michael, Bob here.

589
01:07:07,857 --> 01:07:12,089
Listen, buddy,
you are now nearing Venus...

590
01:07:12,194 --> 01:07:18,724
and your ship is sending
back the most...

591
01:07:18,801 --> 01:07:22,931
beautiful pictures
that I've ever seen.

592
01:07:23,039 --> 01:07:28,102
Buddy, Venus is right outside
your ship right now...

593
01:07:28,210 --> 01:07:32,670
and I-- I wanted
to implore you...

594
01:07:32,748 --> 01:07:35,239
to-- to let me send you
the images.

595
01:07:37,319 --> 01:07:40,777
It's amazing...
Bob out.

596
01:12:27,676 --> 01:12:30,406
This is Michael Forrest
of Life One.

597
01:12:33,882 --> 01:12:36,373
I have just seen Venus.

598
01:12:41,256 --> 01:12:43,724
It's so close,
I feel like I can--

599
01:12:47,930 --> 01:12:50,990
It's so close, I feel like
I can reach out and touch it.

600
01:12:56,572 --> 01:13:00,736
I'm millions of miles
from home.

601
01:13:00,809 --> 01:13:03,505
My only companion is dead.

602
01:13:07,816 --> 01:13:10,785
And I can't help but think...

603
01:13:10,886 --> 01:13:13,286
that I'm the luckiest man alive.

604
01:13:17,593 --> 01:13:22,929
I wish... that you
could see what I see.

605
01:13:29,471 --> 01:13:31,735
This is Life One out.

606
01:13:57,032 --> 01:13:58,829
This is Life One.

607
01:13:58,934 --> 01:14:02,062
Standby for a post-Venus
engine burn.

608
01:14:03,772 --> 01:14:06,798
Arming... in three...

609
01:14:10,045 --> 01:14:11,444
two...

610
01:14:18,387 --> 01:14:19,854
one.

611
01:14:52,921 --> 01:14:54,786
That's the stuff.

612
01:14:57,159 --> 01:15:00,219
Michael? It is official.

613
01:15:00,329 --> 01:15:02,024
The Broncos have won
the Super Bowl.

614
01:15:02,097 --> 01:15:03,496
No, not really.

615
01:15:03,565 --> 01:15:05,328
Uh, you're on
your way home, buddy.

616
01:15:05,400 --> 01:15:07,834
Two more years to go.

617
01:15:07,903 --> 01:15:13,466
Maybe by the time you're home,
you'll be old enough to have
a beer with me.

618
01:15:13,542 --> 01:15:16,010
Sleep well,
'cause I am going to bed.

619
01:15:16,078 --> 01:15:17,841
Bob out.

620
01:15:27,723 --> 01:15:29,714
Life One to Mission Control.

621
01:15:33,228 --> 01:15:37,358
You remember that video
that Moffitt made for me?

622
01:15:37,432 --> 01:15:39,161
Think you could track
that down?

623
01:15:41,470 --> 01:15:44,098
I think I'd like
to see it now.

624
01:15:46,475 --> 01:15:47,567
Thanks.

625
01:15:52,247 --> 01:15:56,343
This message is for
Astronaut Michael Forrest.

626
01:15:56,418 --> 01:16:00,218
My name is Avery Grey.
I'm from Omaha, Nebraska.

627
01:16:12,501 --> 01:16:14,628
Good luck, Michael,
in Chinese.

628
01:16:14,736 --> 01:16:15,794
Hi, Michael...

629
01:16:20,475 --> 01:16:23,638
Astronaut Forrest, I just want
to thank you so much...

630
01:16:23,745 --> 01:16:28,978
for being a tremendous
influence to me and my family.
We're so proud of you.

631
01:16:29,084 --> 01:16:33,953
We wish you a safe return and
you've been a really big
inspiration for all of us.

632
01:16:34,022 --> 01:16:35,284
Please come back safely.

633
01:16:55,877 --> 01:16:59,244
One-- one time, in school...

634
01:16:59,314 --> 01:17:02,181
I was watching
one of your videos...

635
01:17:02,284 --> 01:17:05,947
for a long time,
like, we're talking hours.

636
01:17:06,021 --> 01:17:08,421
Um, and then
this teacher came in...

637
01:17:08,490 --> 01:17:11,482
and she said,
""You're missing science class.""

638
01:17:11,560 --> 01:17:16,497
And then I told her,
""I ain't missing nothing.

639
01:17:16,565 --> 01:17:20,934
""I'm watching Astronaut Michael
Forrest going to search for
space worlds.""

640
01:17:21,003 --> 01:17:22,971
That sounds like science to me.

641
01:17:30,178 --> 01:17:32,442
You're my hero.

642
01:17:37,052 --> 01:17:42,490
Astronaut Forrest,
you are a great hero to the
Japanese people.

643
01:17:42,557 --> 01:17:44,684
You give us hope.

644
01:17:44,760 --> 01:17:49,720
And your great accomplishment
will be edged in the history
of mankind.

645
01:17:49,831 --> 01:17:53,562
Sometimes I wonder
if you're scared.

646
01:17:53,669 --> 01:17:56,229
You don't ever look scared...

647
01:17:56,338 --> 01:18:00,502
but you might get stuck
up there...

648
01:18:00,575 --> 01:18:05,535
and I just wanted to tell you,
don't be scared.

649
01:18:05,614 --> 01:18:08,583
'Cause I'm gonna be
just like you.

650
01:18:08,684 --> 01:18:14,179
And, if you get stuck,
I'll come and get you.

651
01:18:25,434 --> 01:18:27,868
All right,
cross checks are complete.

652
01:18:27,936 --> 01:18:32,373
We've run ten pressure-test
simulations and it appears
that your patch is solid.

653
01:18:32,441 --> 01:18:37,105
The inflatable aero-shell
is 1 00 percent,
was never compromised...

654
01:18:37,212 --> 01:18:40,841
so you've got yourself
a heat shield.

655
01:18:40,916 --> 01:18:43,248
You can start warming up the
capsule for the ride home.

656
01:18:43,318 --> 01:18:45,081
Really, at any time,
all systems are go...

657
01:18:45,153 --> 01:18:48,520
with power generator running
at 99.6 percent.

658
01:18:48,590 --> 01:18:52,583
Truly, a hell of a job, you've
got her purring like a kitten.

659
01:18:55,097 --> 01:18:56,792
So this is it.

660
01:18:56,898 --> 01:18:59,867
Time to say goodbye
to the HAB MOD.

661
01:18:59,935 --> 01:19:02,267
Time to say goodbye
to Life One.

662
01:19:04,439 --> 01:19:06,304
Listen, Michael, um...

663
01:19:06,408 --> 01:19:08,638
I'm proud to have been
here with you.

664
01:19:08,744 --> 01:19:11,872
Thanks, Bob.

665
01:19:11,947 --> 01:19:13,881

I couldn't have done
it without you.

666
01:19:15,851 --> 01:19:18,752
That is so true.

667
01:19:21,423 --> 01:19:23,755
It's been my pleasure.

668
01:19:25,527 --> 01:19:27,722
Okay, standby.

669
01:19:27,796 --> 01:19:30,424
All that's left to do is fire
the engines for the breaking
procedure.

670
01:19:30,499 --> 01:19:32,660
We'll see you after splashdown.

671
01:19:32,768 --> 01:19:34,099
Bob out.

672
01:20:19,247 --> 01:20:22,307
Life One to Mission Control.

673
01:20:22,384 --> 01:20:24,181
Life One to Mission Control.

674
01:20:26,421 --> 01:20:28,048
Mission Control, over.

675
01:20:30,759 --> 01:20:33,557
Jeffs, how you doing, buddy?

676
01:20:33,662 --> 01:20:36,893
Listen, I need to speak
to Mr. Moffitt.

677
01:20:36,998 --> 01:20:39,057
Can you find him for me?

678
01:20:39,167 --> 01:20:41,863
Thanks.

679
01:20:41,937 --> 01:20:43,700
This is Life One out.

680
01:20:49,444 --> 01:20:51,469
What can I do for you,
Michael?

681
01:20:51,546 --> 01:20:53,844
How's the countdown going?

682
01:20:53,915 --> 01:20:57,874
Funny you should ask.
That's actually what I wanted
to talk to you about.

683
01:20:57,953 --> 01:21:00,387
Shoot.

684
01:21:03,425 --> 01:21:06,553
I've decided to abort
the countdown.

685
01:21:10,532 --> 01:21:11,590
What are you saying?

686
01:21:11,700 --> 01:21:13,258
What do you mean abort?

687
01:21:14,736 --> 01:21:18,069
I'm rebooting the mission.

688
01:21:18,139 --> 01:21:20,607
I'm going to Europa.

689
01:21:20,709 --> 01:21:22,836
Wait a minute.

690
01:21:22,911 --> 01:21:25,709
I got a ton of reasons
why that's not gonna work.

691
01:21:25,780 --> 01:21:28,681
Besides, everybody here is
working to get you down safely.

692
01:21:28,750 --> 01:21:32,208

Just listen to me for a second.

693
01:21:35,223 --> 01:21:37,885
There's a reason
I came up here.

694
01:21:41,596 --> 01:21:43,530
Someone's supposed to go.

695
01:21:43,598 --> 01:21:46,226
Someone's supposed to see this.

696
01:21:49,337 --> 01:21:52,204
Michael, I have no button
to bring you down.

697
01:21:55,243 --> 01:21:57,143
You got me.

698
01:21:57,245 --> 01:21:59,213
You got me.
There's nothing I can do.

699
01:22:03,518 --> 01:22:06,783
I thought my life was over
when that accident happened.

700
01:22:09,090 --> 01:22:12,321
The truth is,
I've been living life up here.

701
01:22:13,595 --> 01:22:15,722
I'm gonna continue to live.

702
01:22:19,467 --> 01:22:24,734
Michael...
what was this all for?

703
01:22:24,806 --> 01:22:26,569
See the whales on Europa?

704
01:22:26,641 --> 01:22:29,838
Mr. Moffitt...

705
01:22:29,945 --> 01:22:32,641
you got to learn
to trust me again.

706
01:22:32,714 --> 01:22:34,841
Michael, listen to me.

707
01:22:34,950 --> 01:22:38,317
I don't know how else to put
this, but we gotta lay
Nathan to rest.

708
01:22:38,386 --> 01:22:39,944
We have to.

709
01:22:46,962 --> 01:22:48,657
I just want you home.

710
01:22:51,299 --> 01:22:52,926
You hear me? Michael?

711
01:22:55,670 --> 01:22:59,106
I can't have another death
on my conscience.

712
01:23:01,176 --> 01:23:04,373
Michael? Michael?

713
01:23:31,539 --> 01:23:34,133
This is Michael Forrest
of Life One.

714
01:23:36,778 --> 01:23:40,236
You'll have to forgive me.

715
01:23:40,348 --> 01:23:44,182
I'm not normally a man
of many words...

716
01:23:44,252 --> 01:23:46,482
but I'm doing the best I can.

717
01:23:48,923 --> 01:23:51,551
I wanted to thank all of you...

718
01:23:51,626 --> 01:23:53,184
for your support.

719
01:23:54,796 --> 01:23:57,993
Thought I was alone up here.

720
01:23:58,066 --> 01:23:59,693
I was wrong.

721
01:24:02,904 --> 01:24:06,032
It was about three years ago...

722
01:24:06,107 --> 01:24:09,838
from now that Astronaut
Nathan Miller lost his life.

723
01:24:12,881 --> 01:24:19,218
I lost a colleague,
a fellow astronaut, friend.

724
01:24:19,287 --> 01:24:24,224
But just like all of you,
his spirit never abandoned me.

725
01:24:27,562 --> 01:24:31,191
In a book he brought onboard,
a collection of poems.

726
01:24:31,266 --> 01:24:34,258
He speaks to me.

727
01:24:34,335 --> 01:24:39,967
One passage in particular,
I still hear him loud and clear.

728
01:24:41,309 --> 01:24:44,107
It's by T.S. Eliot.

729
01:24:44,179 --> 01:24:50,118
It says, ""We shall not cease
from exploration.

730
01:24:52,754 --> 01:24:56,815
""And the end of all our
exploring will be to arrive
where we started.

731
01:24:56,925 --> 01:24:59,450
""And know the place
for the first time.

732
01:25:02,464 --> 01:25:05,297
""Through the unknown,
unremembered gate...

733
01:25:05,366 --> 01:25:08,927
""when the last of Earth left to
discover was that which was the
beginning.

